
@startuml

' Define classes and their attributes
class Game {
    - id: String
    + players: List<Player>
    + deck: Deck
    + scoringTable: ScoringTable
}

class Player {
    - id: String
    + name: String
}

class Deck {
    - id: String
    + cards: List<Card>
}

abstract class Card {
    - id: String
    + suit: Suit
    + rank: String
    + compare(other: Card): ComparisonResult
}

enum Suit {
    DIAMONDS, HEARTS, SPADES, CLUBS
}

enum ComparisonResult {
    LOWER, EQUAL, HIGHER
}

class ScoringTable {
    - id: String
    + rounds: List<Round>
}

abstract class Round {
    - id: String
    + winningPlayers: List<Player>
    + points: Integer
}

class JackRound {
    - id: String
}

class SoloRound {
    - id: String
    + soloType: SoloType
    + soloPlayer: Player
}

class MandatorySoloRound {
    - id: String
}

enum SoloType {
    TRUMP, JACK, QUEEN
}

' Inheritance relationships
Card <|-- TrumpCard
Card <|-- QueenCard
Card <|-- JackCard

Deck "1" *-- "0..48" Card : contains

Game "1" *-- "4" Player : has
Game "1" *-- "1" Deck : uses
Game "1" *-- "1" ScoringTable : tracks

ScoringTable "1" *-- "many" Round : contains

Round <|-- JackRound
Round <|-- SoloRound
SoloRound <|-- MandatorySoloRound

@enduml

---

### Notes:
- **Abstract classes** like `Card` and `Round` are marked with `<|--`.
- **Enums** (`Suit`, `ComparisonResult`, `SoloType`) define fixed sets of values.
- **Associations** and **multiplicities** are included to model how many objects are involved in each relationship (e.g., 1 deck has up to 48 cards).
- **MandatorySoloRound** inherits from `SoloRound`, which itself inherits from `Round`.

